content.description: US stocks climbe amid growing bets on interest rate cuts as President Trump appeared to get closer to naming his replacement for Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell.
Unemployment claims remain low despite federal worker layoffs.
Nvidia hits a new record high in 2025, will they keep defying chip shortages and tariffs is the big question.

outlook: Markets react to policy shifts, with retail, tech, and labor trends under close watch; Nvidia's strong momentum continues despite supply and trade pressures; Markets seem to belive a replacement for Jerome Powell will drive further volatility.
